defaultNonetheless, full and regular access to information has been an ongoing issue for the Committee. The Deputy Mayor 
defaultfor Policing and Crime 
defaultinitially insisted that requests for information should be made to MOPAC rather than to the Met
default, since the PCC’s role is to scrutinise MOPAC not the Met,
default 
default&#xa0;
default and said he would assess whether or not the information should be provided. Similarly, he sought to limit appearances by senior Met officers, including the Commissioner, at the Committee. 
defaultWe
default argued that, if 
defaultthe Committee 
defaultneeds information from the Met to fulfil its functions, the Met should provide it directly
default, noting that as Assembly Members we would be entitled to this information if we requested in that capacity anyway
